{"text": "Short and sweet, this game is a wonderful introduction to a series I can't wait to play more of! Trap is a point n' click horror/mystery game with all the classic elements. I personally love the color palette of the game itself, it reminds me of a blood-splattered neon sign from the 80's. The sound design is also fantastic; with sound effects scattered throughout to make your skin crawl and a soundtrack that sets a perfectly spooky, atmospheric scene. The puzzles were fairly simple but fun to figure out. Part 2 is heading to Steam this summer according to the dev. I am very excited for it, so I'll be sure to edit my review to reflect the full experience once I've played that as well.", "appid": "841270", "steamid": "profiles/76561198173569365", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "17", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1530878400.0}
